summary: can we stop trying to make any man that pops in peter parker's life a father figure? he had uncle ben and honestly that was...
body: can we stop trying to make any man that pops in peter parker’s life a father figure? he had uncle ben and honestly that was enough. what he needs is a mentor or just a dependable friend who can be there for him. just because they’re in his life doesn’t mean they have to want to adopt him or treat him like a child to mother. stop trying to project. let people have relationships with people that aren’t so dependent or whatever word i’m looking for here. give peter parker a stupid rich guy who just gives him money and rolls his eyes when peter tells bad jokes and does flips.
